      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks for that. so if my COGS is $500k and my average inventory is $50k, but i found out $10k of that was actually just shrinkage, how does the ratio change? also, what are some of the usual reasons a company sees such a sudden spike in shrinkage like this?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
