      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "With $10k of shrinkage, your adjusted COGS becomes $490k ($500k - $10k), making your new inventory turnover ratio 9.8 ($490k / $50k). Compared to the original 10, this slight reduction shows the direct effect of the lost inventory on your turnover rate. Sudden spikes in shrinkage are often caused by theft (internal or external), process errors leading to spoilage, or incorrect inventory counts during cycle checks. You should investigate security protocols, handling procedures, and recent staff changes to find the root cause.",
