      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "When theft seems random, it can be a sign of opportunistic or internal skimming, rather than a highly organized operation. Look for patterns like consistently higher losses during specific shifts, specific high-value items disappearing, or discrepancies only found during physical audits. If it's organized, you might see a steady, predictable decline over several weeks, whereas simple opportunistic theft can look more erratic. Reviewing access logs and employee movement when those specific items are handled can provide crucial clues.",
